From: OpenAI Codex <codex@openai.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: freescale: dpaa: add Stage 0 FMAN backend dry-run scaffolding

Add the first true hardware-offload control-plane boundary without
steering traffic yet:

- introduce a private FMAN backend state model for dry-run, install,
  remove, and stats follow-on work
- track backend-owned readiness, degradation, and placeholder resource
  lifetime in DPAA
- evaluate hardware-mode candidates through a dry-run-only FMAN backend
  instead of aliasing them into the current DPAA executor
- surface dry-run readiness, degradation class, and FMAN KeyGen scheme
  inventory through ft_offload
- emit rate-limited kernel messages when hardware mode degrades back to
  the normal Linux path

Keep software flow offloading on the existing DPAA executor path.
Keep hardware flow offloading honest: no live FMAN install yet, no
silent fallback into the DPAA executor, and no widening of the accepted
flow contract.

---
